  <description type="morphology">Twigs hairy, often densely so, hairs rusty brown. Leaves: petiole 2–12 mm, hairy to glabrate, glandular at petiole-blade junction, &lt;glands 2&gt;; blade elliptic to obovate, 3–12.5 × 2–6.5 cm, ± leathery, apex usually obtuse, rounded, or emarginate, sometimes abruptly acute or short-acuminate, abaxial surface sparsely hairy, especially along midribs and proximally. Inflorescences: rachises 50–160 mm.</description>
